r, stat logging\n- Collection printing utilities\n\n### 31. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/KeyBlock.java\n\nKey block iterator (140 lines):\n- AbstractSequentialList implementation\n- Provides block of sequential integer keys\n- Custom iterator implementation\n\n### 32. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/FinancialUtils.java\n\nFinancial calculations (113 lines):\n- Gain and gain percent calculations\n- Holdings total computation\n- HTML formatting for gains/losses\n- Uses RoundingMode enum (updated from deprecated BigDecimal constants)\n\n### 33. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/TradeRunTimeModeLiteral.java\n\nRuntime mode literal (36 lines):\n- AnnotationLiteral for RuntimeMode qualifier\n- Used for dynamic CDI bean selection\n\n### 34. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/TradeConfig.java\n\nConfiguration class (425 lines):\n- Runtime modes (Direct JPA, Direct JDBC, Full EJB3, Session to Direct)\n- Order processing modes (Sync, Async, Async 2-Phase)\n- Database scaling parameters (MAX_USERS, MAX_QUOTES)\n- Random data generation\n- Scenario mixing for testing\n- Price change factors and penny stock handling\n\n### 35. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/startup/DatabasePopulator.java\n\nDatabase initialization (150 lines):\n- @ApplicationScoped\n- Observes StartupEvent\n- Populates quotes and users on startup\n- Configurable via application.properties\n- Checks for existing data before populating\n\n### 36. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/messaging/QuoteUpdateMessage.java\n\nQuote update message POJO (195 lines):\n- Replaces JMS TextMessage\n- Commands: updateQuote, ping\n- Full quote information fields\n- Factory methods for message creation\n\n### 37. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/messaging/MessageProducerService.java\n\nMessaging producer service (149 lines):\n- @ApplicationScoped\n- SmallRye Reactive Messaging Emitters\n- Sends to trade-broker-queue and trade-streamer-topic\n- Replaces JMS ConnectionFactory/Queue/Topic pattern\n\n### 38. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/messaging/OrderMessage.java\n\nOrder message POJO (129 lines):\n- Replaces JMS TextMessage for orders\n- Commands: neworder, ping\n- Factory methods for message creation\n- Simple POJO for serialization\n\n### 39. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/mdb/DTStreamer3MDB.java\n\nQuote streamer MDB (137 lines):\n- @ApplicationScoped (migrated from @MessageDriven)\n- @Incoming(\"trade-streamer-topic\") for reactive messaging\n- Processes quote updates and ping messages\n- MDB statistics tracking\n\n### 40. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/mdb/DTBroker3MDB.java\n\nTrade broker MDB (159 lines):\n- @ApplicationScoped with @Transactional\n- @Incoming(\"trade-broker-queue\")\n- Processes order completion and ping messages\n- Exception handling triggers rollback\n\n### 41. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/jaxrs/TradeResource.java\n\nMain REST API (184 lines):\n- @Path(\"trade\")\n- Endpoints for market, login, logout, account, holdings, orders\n- Buy and sell operations\n- User registration\n\n### 42. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/jaxrs/MessagingResource.java\n\nMessaging test API (148 lines):\n- @Path(\"/messaging\")\n- Ping endpoints for broker queue and streamer topic\n- Statistics retrieval and reset\n- Replaces PingServlet2MDBQueue and PingServlet2MDBTopic\n\n### 43. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/jaxrs/QuoteResource.java\n\nQuote API (82 lines):\n- @Path(\"quotes\")\n- GET and POST endpoints for retrieving quotes\n- Comma-separated symbol support\n\n### 44. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/TradeAppResource.java\n\nWeb UI resource (414 lines):\n- @Path(\"/app\")\n- Replaces TradeAppServlet\n- HTML responses (replaces JSPs)\n- Login, home, portfolio, account, quotes pages\n- Buy and sell forms\n- Simple ThreadLocal session simulation\n\n### 45. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/test/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/TradeResourceTest.java\n\nBasic REST API test (20 lines):\n- @QuarkusTest\n- Tests market summary endpoint\n- Uses RestAssured\n\n### 46. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/test/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/messaging/MessagingTest.java\n\nMessaging integration test (110 lines):\n- Tests broker and streamer ping messages\n- Quote update processing\n- Async order processing\n- MDBStats verification\n\n### 47. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/test/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/messaging/MessagingResourceTest.java\n\nMessaging REST API test (120 lines):\n- Tests ping endpoints\n- Statistics endpoints\n- Reset functionality\n- Uses RestAssured with Hamcrest matchers\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nAll 47 Java files have been successfully read. This represents a complete Jakarta EE to Quarkus migration of the IBM DayTrader application, featuring:\n\n- **Entity classes**: 5 JPA entities (Quote, Order, Holding, Account, AccountProfile)\n- **Service implementations**: EJB3, Direct JDBC, and Session-to-Direct modes\n- **Messaging**: Reactive Messaging replacing JMS (2 MDBs, producer service, message POJOs)\n- **REST APIs**: 4 JAX-RS resources for trade operations, quotes, messaging, and web UI\n- **Utilities**: Configuration, logging, statistics, financial calculations\n- **Tests**: 3 test classes using Quarkus test framework\n- **Key migrations**: javax.* → jakarta.*, EJB → CDI, JMS → Reactive Messaging, Servlets → JAX-RS"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0505b85d-7bd5-4c52-85f6-40bd7ce1ee5d","uuid":"bfcadcfa-35f3-4020-82db-167e12c9eeb2"}
