{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PQ2LdZRnD5s3JBWZC2sbHX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\n    17→\n    18→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans.RunStatsDataBean;\n    19→\n    20→public interface TradeDB {\n    21→  \n    22→  /**\n    23→   * Reset the TradeData by - removing all newly registered users by scenario\n    24→   * servlet (i.e. users with userID's beginning with \"ru:\") * - removing all\n    25→   * buy/sell order pairs - setting logoutCount = loginCount\n    26→   *\n    27→   * return statistics for this benchmark run\n    28→   */\n    29→  RunStatsDataBean resetTrade(boolean deleteAll) throws Exception;\n    30→\n    31→  /**\n    32→   * Get the Database Product Name\n    33→   *\n    34→   * return DB Product Name String\n    35→   */\n    36→  String checkDBProductName() throws Exception;\n    37→\n    38→  /**\n    39→   * Get the impl for the TradeService\n    40→   *\n    41→   * return int matching the implementation\n    42→   */\n    43→\n    44→}\n    45→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GXMEe2L2LoFwh8taupKyQ7","session_id":"0505b85d-7bd5-4c52-85f6-40bd7ce1ee5d","uuid":"45da1536-ed06-4b06-b614-730e4401aea6"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01C9ZgQvBi9uZM6LJ8GwJmRJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/*******************************************************************************\n     2→* Copyright (c) 2017 IBM Corp.\n     3→*\n     4→* Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→* you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→* You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→*\n     8→*    http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→*\n    10→* Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→* distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→* WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→* See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→* limitations under the License.\n    15→*******************************************************************************/\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\n    17→\n    18→import java.lang.annotation.ElementType;\n    19→import java.lang.annotation.Retention;\n    20→import java.lang.annotation.RetentionPolicy;\n    21→import java.lang.annotation.Target;\n    22→import jakarta.inject.Qualifier;\n    23→\n    24→@Qualifier\n    25→@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\n    26→@Target({ElementType.TYPE, ElementType.METHOD,\n    27→ ElementType.FIELD, ElementType.PARAMETER})\n    28→public @interface RuntimeMode {\n    29→  /**\n    30→  * Default to jaxrs client impl\n    31→  */  \n    32→  String value() default \"Full EJB3\";\n    33→}\n    34→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GXMEe2L2LoFwh8taupKyQ7","session_id":"0505b85d-7bd5-4c52-85f6-40bd7ce1ee5d","uuid":"1c0ed9a0-b84a-49db-89a4-2e99e95167e9"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019KmyWwfjZSiYYHg311JYiF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\n    17→\n    18→import java.lang.annotation.ElementType;\n    19→import java.lang.annotation.Retention;\n    20→import java.lang.annotation.RetentionPolicy;\n    21→import java.lang.annotation.Target;\n    22→import jakarta.inject.Qualifier;\n    23→\n    24→@Qualifier\n    25→@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\n    26→@Target({ElementType.METHOD, ElementType.FIELD, ElementType.PARAMETER, ElementType.TYPE})\n    27→public @interface QuotePriceChange {\n    28→}\n    29→\n    30→\n    31→\n    32→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GXMEe2L2LoFwh8taupKyQ7","session_id":"0505b85d-7bd5-4c52-85f6-40bd7ce1ee5d","uuid":"2a97f80b-9155-40ac-9c30-8f3cce38ee54"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014hMBjxNnzecLAhmet2ntcF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\n    17→\n    18→import java.lang.annotation.ElementType;\n    19→import java.lang.annotation.Retention;\n    20→import java.lang.annotation.RetentionPolicy;\n    21→import java.lang.annotation.Target;\n    22→import jakarta.inject.Qualifier;\n    23→\n    24→@Qualifier\n    25→@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\n    26→@Target({ElementType.METHOD, ElementType.FIELD, ElementType.PARAMETER, ElementType.TYPE})\n    27→public @interface MarketSummaryUpdate {}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GXMEe2L2LoFwh8taupKyQ7","session_id":"0505b85d-7bd5-4c52-85f6-40bd7ce1ee5d","uuid":"1a648cfb-1e92-4d09-af9a-7e3b36cac15f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Vcz948V1RPpiyKq7mVy5LQ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\n    17→\n    18→import java.lang.annotation.Retention;\n    19→import java.lang.annotation.Target;\n    20→\n    21→import jakarta.inject.Qualifier;\n    22→\n    23→import static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.FIELD;\n    24→import static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.METHOD;\n    25→import static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.PARAMETER;\n    26→import static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.TYPE;\n    27→import static java.lang.annotation.RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME;\n    28→\n    29→@Qualifier\n    30→@Retention(RUNTIME)\n    31→@Target({TYPE, METHOD, FIELD, PARAMETER})\n    32→public @interface TradeSession2Direct {}\n    33→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GXMEe2L2LoFwh8taupKyQ7","session_id":"0505b85d-7bd5-4c52-85f6-40bd7ce1ee5d","uuid":"0b21452f-402b-4c46-9158-7340881c834d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WsyveH9nF9hZLNCnNJeprB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→import java.util.Collection;\n    20→import java.util.concurrent.Future;\n    21→\n    22→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans.MarketSummaryDataBean;\n    23→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\n    24→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\n    25→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\n    26→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.OrderDataBean;\n    27→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    28→\n    29→/**\n    30→ * TradeServices interface specifies the business methods provided by the Trade\n    31→ * online broker application. These business methods represent the features and\n    32→ * operations that can be performed by customers of the brokerage such as login,\n    33→ * logout, get a stock quote, buy or sell a stock, etc. This interface is\n    34→ * implemented by {@link Trade} providing an EJB implementation of these\n    35→ * business methods and also by {@link TradeDirect} providing a JDBC\n    36→ * implementation.\n    37→ *\n    38→ * @see TradeDirect\n    39→ * @see TradeSLSB\n    40→ *\n    41→ */\n    42→\n    43→public interface TradeServices {\n    44→\n    45→    /**\n    46→     * Compute and return a snapshot of the current market conditions This\n    47→     * includes the TSIA - an index of the price of the top 100 Trade stock\n    48→     * quotes The openTSIA ( the index at the open) The volume of shares traded,\n    49→     * Top Stocks gain and loss\n    50→     *\n    51→     * @return A snapshot of the current market summary\n    52→     */\n    53→    MarketSummaryDataBean getMarketSummary() throws Exception;\n    54→\n    55→    /**\n    56→     * Create an order (buy or sell)\n    57→     *\n    58→     * @param accoount\n    59→     *            the accountdatabean\n    60→     * @param quote\n    61→     *            the quptedatabean\n    62→     * @param holding\n    63→     *            the holdingdatabean\n    64→     * @param orderType\n    65→     *            buy or sell\n    66→     * @param quantity\n    67→     *            quantity            \n    68→     * @return Collection OrderDataBeans providing detailed order information\n    69→     */\n    70→    OrderDataBean createOrder(AccountDataBean account, QuoteDataBean quote, HoldingDataBean holding, String orderType,\n    71→        double quantity) throws Exception;\n    72→    \n    73→    /**\n    74→     * Purchase a stock and create a new holding for the given user. Given a\n    75→     * stock symbol and quantity to purchase, retrieve the current quote price,\n    76→     * debit the user's account balance, and add holdings to user's portfolio.\n    77→     * buy/sell are asynchronous, using J2EE messaging, A new order is created\n    78→     * and submitted for processing to the TradeBroker\n    79→     *\n    80→     * @param userID\n    81→     *            the customer requesting the stock purchase\n    82→     * @param symbol\n    83→     *            the symbol of the stock being purchased\n    84→     * @param quantity\n    85→     *            the quantity of shares to purchase\n    86→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the newly created buy order\n    87→     */\n    88→\n    89→    OrderDataBean buy(String userID, String symbol, double quantity, int orderProcessingMode) throws Exception;\n    90→\n    91→    /**\n    92→     * Sell a stock holding and removed the holding for the given user. Given a\n    93→     * Holding, retrieve current quote, credit user's account, and reduce\n    94→     * holdings in user's portfolio.\n    95→     *\n    96→     * @param userID\n    97→     *            the customer requesting the sell\n    98→     * @param holdingID\n    99→     *            the users holding to be sold\n   100→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the newly created sell\n   101→     *         order\n   102→     */\n   103→    OrderDataBean sell(String userID, Integer holdingID, int orderProcessingMode) throws Exception;\n   104→\n   105→    /**\n   106→     * Queue the Order identified by orderID to be processed\n   107→     *\n   108→     * Orders are submitted through JMS to a Trading Broker and completed\n   109→     * asynchronously. This method queues the order for processing\n   110→     *\n   111→     * The boolean twoPhase specifies to the server implementation whether or\n   112→     * not the method is to participate in a global transaction\n   113→     *\n   114→     * @param orderID\n   115→     *            the Order being queued for processing\n   116→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the completed order\n   117→     */\n   118→    void queueOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception;\n   119→\n   120→    /**\n   121→     * Complete the Order identified by orderID. This method completes\n   122→     * the order For a buy, the stock is purchased creating a holding and the\n   123→     * users account is debited For a sell, the stock holding is removed and the\n   124→     * users account is credited with the proceeds\n   125→     *\n   126→     * The boolean twoPhase specifies to the server implementation whether or\n   127→     * not the method is to participate in a global transaction\n   128→     *\n   129→     * @param orderID\n   130→     *            the Order to complete\n   131→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the completed order\n   132→     */\n   133→    OrderDataBean completeOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception;\n   134→\n   135→    /**\n   136→     * Complete the Order identefied by orderID Orders are completed \n   137→     * asynchronously. This method completes\n   138→     * the order For a buy, the stock is purchased creating a holding and the\n   139→     * users account is debited For a sell, the stock holding is removed and the\n   140→     * users account is credited with the proceeds\n   141→     *\n   142→     * The boolean twoPhase specifies to the server implementation whether or\n   143→     * not the method is to participate in a global transaction\n   144→     *\n   145→     * @param orderID\n   146→     *            the Order to complete\n   147→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the completed order\n   148→     */\n   149→    Future<OrderDataBean> completeOrderAsync(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception;\n   150→    \n   151→    /**\n   152→     * Cancel the Order identefied by orderID\n   153→     *\n   154→     * The boolean twoPhase specifies to the server implementation whether or\n   155→     * not the method is to participate in a global transaction\n   156→     *\n   157→     * @param orderID\n   158→     *            the Order to complete\n   159→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the completed order\n   160→     */\n   161→    void cancelOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception;\n   162→\n   163→    /**\n   164→     * Signify an order has been completed for the given userID\n   165→     *\n   166→     * @param userID\n   167→     *            the user for which an order has completed\n   168→     * @param orderID\n   169→     *            the order which has completed\n   170→     *\n   171→     */\n   172→    void orderCompleted(String userID, Integer orderID) throws Exception;\n   173→\n   174→    /**\n   175→     * Get the collection of all orders for a given account\n   176→     *\n   177→     * @param userID\n   178→     *            the customer account to retrieve orders for\n   179→     * @return Collection OrderDataBeans providing detailed order information\n   180→     */\n   181→    Collection<?> getOrders(String userID) throws Exception;\n   182→\n   183→    /**\n   184→     * Get the collection of completed orders for a given account that need to\n   185→     * be alerted to the user\n   186→     *\n   187→     * @param userID\n   188→     *            the customer account to retrieve orders for\n   189→     * @return Collection OrderDataBeans providing detailed order information\n   190→     */\n   191→    Collection<?> getClosedOrders(String userID) throws Exception;\n   192→\n   193→    /**\n   194→     * Given a market symbol, price, and details, create and return a new\n   195→     * {@link QuoteDataBean}\n   196→     *\n   197→     * @param symbol\n   198→     *            the symbol of the stock\n   199→     * @param price\n   200→     *            the current stock price\n   201→     * @param details\n   202→     *            a short description of the stock or company\n   203→     * @return a new QuoteDataBean or null if Quote could not be created\n   204→     */\n   205→    QuoteDataBean createQuote(String symbol, String companyName, BigDecimal price) throws Exception;\n   206→\n   207→    /**\n   208→     * Return a {@link QuoteDataBean} describing a current quote for the given\n   209→     * stock symbol\n   210→     *\n   211→     * @param symbol\n   212→     *            the stock symbol to retrieve the current Quote\n   213→     * @return the QuoteDataBean\n   214→     */\n   215→    QuoteDataBean getQuote(String symbol) throws Exception;\n   216→\n   217→    /**\n   218→     * Return a {@link java.util.Collection} of {@link QuoteDataBean} describing\n   219→     * all current quotes\n   220→     *\n   221→     * @return A collection of QuoteDataBean\n   222→     */\n   223→    Collection<?> getAllQuotes() throws Exception;\n   224→\n   225→    /**\n   226→     * Update the stock quote price and volume for the specified stock symbol\n   227→     *\n   228→     * @param symbol\n   229→     *            for stock quote to update\n   230→     * @param price\n   231→     *            the updated quote price\n   232→     * @return the QuoteDataBean describing the stock\n   233→     */\n   234→    QuoteDataBean updateQuotePriceVolume(String symbol, BigDecimal newPrice, double sharesTraded) throws Exception;\n   235→\n   236→    /**\n   237→     * Return the portfolio of stock holdings for the specified customer as a\n   238→     * collection of HoldingDataBeans\n   239→     *\n   240→     * @param userID\n   241→     *            the customer requesting the portfolio\n   242→     * @return Collection of the users portfolio of stock holdings\n   243→     */\n   244→    Collection<HoldingDataBean> getHoldings(String userID) throws Exception;\n   245→\n   246→    /**\n   247→     * Return a specific user stock holding identifed by the holdingID\n   248→     *\n   249→     * @param holdingID\n   250→     *            the holdingID to return\n   251→     * @return a HoldingDataBean describing the holding\n   252→     */\n   253→    HoldingDataBean getHolding(Integer holdingID) throws Exception;\n   254→\n   255→    /**\n   256→     * Return an AccountDataBean object for userID describing the account\n   257→     *\n   258→     * @param userID\n   259→     *            the account userID to lookup\n   260→     * @return User account data in AccountDataBean\n   261→     */\n   262→    AccountDataBean getAccountData(String userID) throws Exception;\n   263→\n   264→    /**\n   265→     * Return an AccountProfileDataBean for userID providing the users profile\n   266→     *\n   267→     * @param userID\n   268→     *            the account userID to lookup\n   269→     * @param User\n   270→     *            account profile data in AccountProfileDataBean\n   271→     */\n   272→    AccountProfileDataBean getAccountProfileData(String userID) throws Exception;\n   273→\n   274→    /**\n   275→     * Update userID's account profile information using the provided\n   276→     * AccountProfileDataBean object\n   277→     *\n   278→     * @param userID\n   279→     *            the account userID to lookup\n   280→     * @param User\n   281→     *            account profile data in AccountProfileDataBean\n   282→     */\n   283→    AccountProfileDataBean updateAccountProfile(AccountProfileDataBean profileData) throws Exception;\n   284→\n   285→    /**\n   286→     * Attempt to authenticate and login a user with the given password\n   287→     *\n   288→     * @param userID\n   289→     *            the customer to login\n   290→     * @param password\n   291→     *            the password entered by the customer for authentication\n   292→     * @return User account data in AccountDataBean\n   293→     */\n   294→    AccountDataBean login(String userID, String password) throws Exception;\n   295→\n   296→    /**\n   297→     * Logout the given user\n   298→     *\n   299→     * @param userID\n   300→     *            the customer to logout\n   301→     * @return the login status\n   302→     */\n   303→\n   304→    void logout(String userID) throws Exception;\n   305→\n   306→    /**\n   307→     * Register a new Trade customer. Create a new user profile, user registry\n   308→     * entry, account with initial balance, and empty portfolio.\n   309→     *\n   310→     * @param userID\n   311→     *            the new customer to register\n   312→     * @param password\n   313→     *            the customers password\n   314→     * @param fullname\n   315→     *            the customers fullname\n   316→     * @param address\n   317→     *            the customers street address\n   318→     * @param email\n   319→     *            the customers email address\n   320→     * @param creditcard\n   321→     *            the customers creditcard number\n   322→     * @param initialBalance\n   323→     *            the amount to charge to the customers credit to open the\n   324→     *            account and set the initial balance\n   325→     * @return the userID if successful, null otherwise\n   326→     */\n   327→    AccountDataBean register(String userID, String password, String fullname, String address, String email, String creditcard, BigDecimal openBalance)\n   328→            throws Exception;\n   329→\n   330→    \n   331→    int getImpl();\n   332→\n   333→    QuoteDataBean pingTwoPhase(String symbol) throws Exception;\n   334→\n   335→    double investmentReturn(double rnd1, double rnd2) throws Exception;\n   336→\n   337→    void setInSession(boolean inSession);\n   338→}\n   339→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GXMEe2L2LoFwh8taupKyQ7","session_id":"0505b85d-7bd5-4c52-85f6-40bd7ce1ee5d","uuid":"20c8d999-a2f9-4caa-b8b5-bbe990ef4ce8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01F31HQMgrZZaPdvx28r2g11","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\n    17→\n    18→import java.lang.annotation.Retention;\n    19→import java.lang.annotation.Target;\n    20→\n    21→import jakarta.inject.Qualifier;\n    22→\n    23→import static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.FIELD;\n    24→import static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.METHOD;\n    25→import static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.PARAMETER;\n    26→import static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.TYPE;\n    27→import static java.lang.annotation.RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME;\n    28→\n    29→@Qualifier\n    30→@Retention(RUNTIME)\n    31→@Target({TYPE, METHOD, FIELD, PARAMETER})\n    32→public @interface TradeJDBC {}\n    33→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GXMEe2L2LoFwh8taupKyQ7","session_id":"0505b85d-7bd5-4c52-85f6-40bd7ce1ee5d","uuid":"04a5e105-f0e0-4159-8ddb-cd8c53ac70e8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QWAsEPMcxcnrJNc3iQDzXG","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→import jakarta.enterprise.util.AnnotationLiteral;\n    19→\n    20→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.RuntimeMode;\n    21→\n    22→public class TradeRunTimeModeLiteral extends AnnotationLiteral<RuntimeMode> implements RuntimeMode {\n    23→  \n    24→  private static final long serialVersionUID = -252789556335033400L;\n    25→    private String value;\n    26→    public TradeRunTimeModeLiteral(String value) {\n    27→        this.value = value;\n    28→    }\n    29→\n    30→    @Override\n    31→    public String value() {\n    32→         return value;\n    33→    }\n    34→\n    35→}\n    36→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GXMEe2L2LoFwh8taupKyQ7","session_id":"0505b85d-7bd5-4c52-85f6-40bd7ce1ee5d","uuid":"71a3af0a-671b-43c3-8449-ad9cb7ff01f2"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0152turaqXBdbzxV4pPScs56","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→import java.util.List;\n    18→import java.util.concurrent.CopyOnWriteArrayList;\n    19→\n    20→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    21→import jakarta.enterprise.event.Event;\n    22→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    23→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotEmpty;\n    24→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    25→import jakarta.validation.constraints.Size;\n    26→\n    27→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    28→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.QuotePriceChange;\n    29→\n    30→\n    31→/** This class is a holds the last 5 stock changes, used by the MarketSummary WebSocket\n    32→ *  and the JAX-RS SSE Broadcaster\n    33→ *  It fires a CDI event everytime a price change is added\n    34→ **/\n    35→\n    36→@ApplicationScoped\n    37→public class RecentQuotePriceChangeList  {\n    38→\n    39→  private List<QuoteDataBean> list = new CopyOnWriteArrayList<QuoteDataBean>();\n    40→  private int maxSize = 5;\n    41→\n    42→  @Inject\n    43→  @QuotePriceChange\n    44→  Event<String> quotePriceChangeEvent;\n    45→\n    46→  public boolean add(QuoteDataBean quoteData) {\n    47→\n    48→    int symbolNumber = new Integer(quoteData.getSymbol().substring(2));\n    49→\n    50→    if ( symbolNumber < TradeConfig.getMAX_QUOTES() * TradeConfig.getListQuotePriceChangeFrequency() * 0.01) {\n    51→      list.add(0, quoteData);\n    52→\n    53→      // Add stock, remove if needed\n    54→      if(list.size() > maxSize) {\n    55→        list.remove(maxSize);\n    56→      }      \n    57→      // Fire async event without ManagedExecutorService (Quarkus handles async events differently)\n    58→      quotePriceChangeEvent.fireAsync(\"quotePriceChange for symbol: \" + quoteData.getSymbol());\n    59→    }\n    60→    return true;\n    61→  }\n    62→\n    63→  public boolean isEmpty() {\n    64→    return list.isEmpty();\n    65→  }\n    66→\n    67→  @Size(max=5)\n    68→  @NotEmpty\n    69→  public List<@NotNull QuoteDataBean> recentList() {\n    70→    return list;\n    71→  }\n    72→}\n    73→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GXMEe2L2LoFwh8taupKyQ7","session_id":"0505b85d-7bd5-4c52-85f6-40bd7ce1ee5d","uuid":"a51c10b4-62df-4c08-8678-f67c4569c468"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HuWTCbwrkoxCLNr8VXBfBz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→import java.math.RoundingMode;\n    20→import java.util.Collection;\n    21→\n    22→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\n    23→\n    24→/**\n    25→ * MIGRATION NOTE: Updated to use RoundingMode enum instead of deprecated BigDecimal constants.\n    26→ */\n    27→public class FinancialUtils {\n    28→\n    29→    public static final RoundingMode ROUND = RoundingMode.HALF_UP;\n    30→    public static final int SCALE = 2;\n    31→    public static final BigDecimal ZERO = new BigDecimal(\"0.00\").setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n    32→    public static final BigDecimal ONE = new BigDecimal(\"1.00\").setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n    33→    public static final BigDecimal HUNDRED = new BigDecimal(\"100.00\").setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n    34→\n    35→    public static BigDecimal computeGain(BigDecimal currentBalance, BigDecimal openBalance) {\n    36→        return currentBalance.subtract(openBalance).setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n    37→    }\n    38→\n    39→    public static BigDecimal computeGainPercent(BigDecimal currentBalance, BigDecimal openBalance) {\n    40→        if (openBalance.doubleValue() == 0.0) {\n    41→            return ZERO;\n    42→        }\n    43→        BigDecimal gainPercent = currentBalance.divide(openBalance, SCALE, ROUND)\n    44→                .subtract(ONE)\n    45→                .multiply(HUNDRED);\n    46→        return gainPercent;\n    47→    }\n    48→\n    49→    public static BigDecimal computeHoldingsTotal(Collection<?> holdingDataBeans) {\n    50→        BigDecimal holdingsTotal = new BigDecimal(\"0.0\").setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n    51→        if (holdingDataBeans == null) {\n    52→            return holdingsTotal;\n    53→        }\n    54→        for (Object obj : holdingDataBeans) {\n    55→            HoldingDataBean holdingData = (HoldingDataBean) obj;\n    56→            BigDecimal total = holdingData.getPurchasePrice()\n    57→                    .multiply(new BigDecimal(holdingData.getQuantity()));\n    58→            holdingsTotal = holdingsTotal.add(total);\n    59→        }\n    60→        return holdingsTotal.setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n    61→    }\n    62→\n    63→    public static String printGainHTML(BigDecimal gain) {\n    64→        String htmlString, arrow;\n    65→        if (gain.doubleValue() < 0.0) {\n    66→            htmlString = \"<FONT color=\\\"#ff0000\\\">\";\n    67→            arrow = \"arrowdown.gif\";\n    68→        } else {\n    69→            htmlString = \"<FONT color=\\\"#009900\\\">\";\n    70→            arrow = \"arrowup.gif\";\n    71→        }\n    72→\n    73→        htmlString += gain.setScale(SCALE, ROUND) + \"</FONT><IMG src=\\\"images/\" + arrow \n    74→                + \"\\\" width=\\\"10\\\" height=\\\"10\\\" border=\\\"0\\\"></IMG>\";\n    75→        return htmlString;\n    76→    }\n    77→\n    78→    public static String printChangeHTML(double change) {\n    79→        String htmlString, arrow;\n    80→        if (change < 0.0) {\n    81→            htmlString = \"<FONT color=\\\"#ff0000\\\">\";\n    82→            arrow = \"arrowdown.gif\";\n    83→        } else {\n    84→            htmlString = \"<FONT color=\\\"#009900\\\">\";\n    85→            arrow = \"arrowup.gif\";\n    86→        }\n    87→\n    88→        htmlString += change + \"</FONT><IMG src=\\\"images/\" + arrow \n    89→                + \"\\\" width=\\\"10\\\" height=\\\"10\\\" border=\\\"0\\\"></IMG>\";\n    90→        return htmlString;\n    91→    }\n    92→\n    93→    public static String printGainPercentHTML(BigDecimal gain) {\n    94→        String htmlString, arrow;\n    95→        if (gain.doubleValue() < 0.0) {\n    96→            htmlString = \"(<B><FONT color=\\\"#ff0000\\\">\";\n    97→            arrow = \"arrowdown.gif\";\n    98→        } else {\n    99→            htmlString = \"(<B><FONT color=\\\"#009900\\\">+\";\n   100→            arrow = \"arrowup.gif\";\n   101→        }\n   102→\n   103→        htmlString += gain.setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n   104→        htmlString += \"%</FONT></B>)<IMG src=\\\"images/\" + arrow \n   105→                + \"\\\" width=\\\"10\\\" height=\\\"10\\\" border=\\\"0\\\"></IMG>\";\n   106→        return htmlString;\n   107→    }\n   108→\n   109→    public static String printQuoteLink(String symbol) {\n   110→        return \"<A href=\\\"app?action=quotes&symbols=\" + symbol + \"\\\">\" + symbol + \"</A>\";\n   111→    }\n   112→}\n   113→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GXMEe2L2LoFwh8taupKyQ7","session_id":"0505b85d-7bd5-4c52-85f6-40bd7ce1ee5d","uuid":"84753e51-d2c7-4c0d-a516-95ff38f22f8a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01992BoehE8VZvyB6c48J7ff","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.Serializable;\n    19→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    20→\n    21→// MIGRATION: javax.* -> jakarta.*\n    22→import jakarta.persistence.Column;\n    23→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n    24→import jakarta.persistence.Id;\n    25→import jakarta.persistence.NamedNativeQueries;\n    26→import jakarta.persistence.NamedNativeQuery;\n    27→import jakarta.persistence.NamedQueries;\n    28→import jakarta.persistence.NamedQuery;\n    29→import jakarta.persistence.Table;\n    30→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n    31→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    32→import jakarta.validation.constraints.Positive;\n    33→\n    34→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    35→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    36→\n    37→@Entity(name = \"quoteejb\")\n    38→@Table(name = \"quoteejb\")\n    39→@NamedQueries({\n    40→    @NamedQuery(name = \"quoteejb.allQuotes\", query = \"SELECT q FROM quoteejb q\")\n    41→})\n    42→@NamedNativeQueries({\n    43→    @NamedNativeQuery(name = \"quoteejb.quoteForUpdate\", \n    44→        query = \"select * from quoteejb q where q.symbol=? for update\", \n    45→        resultClass = QuoteDataBean.class)\n    46→})\n    47→public class QuoteDataBean implements Serializable {\n    48→\n    49→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1847932261895838791L;\n    50→\n    51→    @Id\n    52→    @NotNull\n    53→    @Column(name = \"SYMBOL\", nullable = false)\n    54→    private String symbol;\n    55→\n    56→    @Column(name = \"COMPANYNAME\")\n    57→    @NotBlank\n    58→    private String companyName;\n    59→\n    60→    @NotNull\n    61→    @Column(name = \"VOLUME\", nullable = false)\n    62→    private double volume;\n    63→\n    64→    @Column(name = \"PRICE\")\n    65→    @Positive\n    66→    private BigDecimal price;\n    67→\n    68→    @Column(name = \"OPEN1\")\n    69→    @Positive\n    70→    private BigDecimal open1;\n    71→\n    72→    @Column(name = \"LOW\")\n    73→    @Positive\n    74→    private BigDecimal low;\n    75→\n    76→    @Column(name = \"HIGH\")\n    77→    @Positive\n    78→    private BigDecimal high;\n    79→\n    80→    @NotNull\n    81→    @Column(name = \"CHANGE1\", nullable = false)\n    82→    private double change1;\n    83→\n    84→    public QuoteDataBean() {\n    85→    }\n    86→\n    87→    public QuoteDataBean(String symbol, String companyName, double volume, \n    88→            BigDecimal price, BigDecimal open, BigDecimal low, \n    89→            BigDecimal high, double change) {\n    90→        setSymbol(symbol);\n    91→        setCompanyName(companyName);\n    92→        setVolume(volume);\n    93→        setPrice(price);\n    94→        setOpen(open);\n    95→        setLow(low);\n    96→        setHigh(high);\n    97→        setChange(change);\n    98→    }\n    99→\n   100→    public static QuoteDataBean getRandomInstance() {\n   101→        return new QuoteDataBean(\n   102→            TradeConfig.rndSymbol(),\n   103→            TradeConfig.rndSymbol() + \" Incorporated\",\n   104→            TradeConfig.rndFloat(100000),\n   105→            TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000.0f),\n   106→            TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000.0f),\n   107→            TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000.0f),\n   108→            TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000.0f),\n   109→            TradeConfig.rndFloat(100000)\n   110→        );\n   111→    }\n   112→\n   113→    public QuoteDataBean(String symbol) {\n   114→        setSymbol(symbol);\n   115→    }\n   116→\n   117→    @Override\n   118→    public String toString() {\n   119→        return \"\\n\\tQuote Data for: \" + getSymbol() \n   120→            + \"\\n\\t\\t companyName: \" + getCompanyName() \n   121→            + \"\\n\\t\\t      volume: \" + getVolume() \n   122→            + \"\\n\\t\\t       price: \" + getPrice() \n   123→            + \"\\n\\t\\t        open1: \" + getOpen() \n   124→            + \"\\n\\t\\t         low: \" + getLow() \n   125→            + \"\\n\\t\\t        high: \" + getHigh()\n   126→            + \"\\n\\t\\t      change1: \" + getChange();\n   127→    }\n   128→\n   129→    public String toHTML() {\n   130→        return \"<BR>Quote Data for: \" + getSymbol() \n   131→            + \"<LI> companyName: \" + getCompanyName() + \"</LI>\" \n   132→            + \"<LI>      volume: \" + getVolume() + \"</LI>\"\n   133→            + \"<LI>       price: \" + getPrice() + \"</LI>\" \n   134→            + \"<LI>        open1: \" + getOpen() + \"</LI>\" \n   135→            + \"<LI>         low: \" + getLow() + \"</LI>\"\n   136→            + \"<LI>        high: \" + getHigh() + \"</LI>\" \n   137→            + \"<LI>      change1: \" + getChange() + \"</LI>\";\n   138→    }\n   139→\n   140→    public void print() {\n   141→        Log.log(this.toString());\n   142→    }\n   143→\n   144→    public String getSymbol() {\n   145→        return symbol;\n   146→    }\n   147→\n   148→    public void setSymbol(String symbol) {\n   149→   