{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MuU8so54LmF1vdbF26M6eN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→\n    20→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    21→import jakarta.enterprise.event.Event;\n    22→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    23→\n    24→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    25→\n    26→/**\n    27→ * MIGRATION: Quarkus SmallRye Reactive Messaging -> Jakarta EE CDI Events\n    28→ *\n    29→ * In the Quarkus version, this used @Channel + Emitter from SmallRye Reactive Messaging.\n    30→ * In Jakarta EE, we use CDI Events to decouple the message producer from consumers.\n    31→ * The DTBroker3MDB and DTStreamer3MDB observe these events.\n    32→ */\n    33→@ApplicationScoped\n    34→public class MessageProducerService {\n    35→\n    36→    @Inject\n    37→    Event<OrderMessage> brokerEvent;\n    38→\n    39→    @Inject\n    40→    Event<QuoteUpdateMessage> streamerEvent;\n    41→\n    42→    public void queueOrderForProcessing(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) {\n    43→        OrderMessage message = OrderMessage.newOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n    44→        Log.trace(\"MessageProducerService:queueOrderForProcessing - sending order \" + orderID);\n    45→        brokerEvent.fireAsync(message);\n    46→    }\n    47→\n    48→    public void sendBrokerPing(String text) {\n    49→        OrderMessage message = OrderMessage.ping(text);\n    50→        Log.trace(\"MessageProducerService:sendBrokerPing - sending ping\");\n    51→        brokerEvent.fireAsync(message);\n    52→    }\n    53→\n    54→    public void publishQuoteUpdate(String symbol, BigDecimal newPrice, BigDecimal oldPrice) {\n    55→        QuoteUpdateMessage message = QuoteUpdateMessage.quoteUpdate(symbol, newPrice, oldPrice);\n    56→        Log.trace(\"MessageProducerService:publishQuoteUpdate - publishing update for \" + symbol);\n    57→        streamerEvent.fireAsync(message);\n    58→    }\n    59→\n    60→    public void publishQuotePriceChange(String symbol, String company, BigDecimal price,\n    61→            BigDecimal oldPrice, BigDecimal open, BigDecimal low, BigDecimal high,\n    62→            double volume, BigDecimal changeFactor, double sharesTraded) {\n    63→        QuoteUpdateMessage message = QuoteUpdateMessage.quoteUpdate(symbol, price, oldPrice);\n    64→        message.setCompany(company);\n    65→        message.setOpen(open);\n    66→        message.setLow(low);\n    67→        message.setHigh(high);\n    68→        message.setVolume(volume);\n    69→        message.setChangeFactor(changeFactor);\n    70→        message.setSharesTraded(sharesTraded);\n    71→        Log.trace(\"MessageProducerService:publishQuotePriceChange - publishing update for \" + symbol);\n    72→        streamerEvent.fireAsync(message);\n    73→    }\n    74→\n    75→    public void sendStreamerPing(String text) {\n    76→        QuoteUpdateMessage message = QuoteUpdateMessage.ping(text);\n    77→        Log.trace(\"MessageProducerService:sendStreamerPing - sending ping\");\n    78→        streamerEvent.fireAsync(message);\n    79→    }\n    80→}\n    81→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0505b85d-7bd5-4c52-85f6-40bd7ce1ee5d","uuid":"0364f2b4-5812-4895-a60e-d6e69aeba915"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018vdyJhwE4zr35MzET4jHei","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.ejb3;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    20→import java.util.List;\n    21→\n    22→import jakarta.ejb.Singleton;\n    23→import jakarta.ejb.Schedule;\n    24→import jakarta.ejb.Lock;\n    25→import jakarta.ejb.LockType;\n    26→import jakarta.enterprise.event.Event;\n    27→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    28→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n    29→import jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n    30→import jakarta.persistence.TypedQuery;\n    31→import jakarta.persistence.criteria.CriteriaBuilder;\n    32→import jakarta.persistence.criteria.CriteriaQuery;\n    33→import jakarta.persistence.criteria.Root;\n    34→\n    35→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans.MarketSummaryDataBean;\n    36→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    37→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.MarketSummaryUpdate;\n    38→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.FinancialUtils;\n    39→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    40→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    41→\n    42→@Singleton\n    43→public class MarketSummarySingleton {\n    44→\n    45→  private volatile MarketSummaryDataBean marketSummaryDataBean;\n    46→\n    47→  @PersistenceContext(unitName = \"daytrader\")\n    48→  EntityManager entityManager;\n    49→\n    50→  @Inject\n    51→  @MarketSummaryUpdate\n    52→  Event<String> mkSummaryUpdateEvent;\n    53→\n    54→  @Schedule(second = \"*/20\", minute = \"*\", hour = \"*\", persistent = false)\n    55→  public void updateMarketSummary() {\n    56→    Log.trace(\"MarketSummarySingleton:updateMarketSummary -- updating market summary\");\n    57→\n    58→    if (TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode() != TradeConfig.EJB3) {\n    59→      Log.trace(\"MarketSummarySingleton:updateMarketSummary -- Not EJB3 Mode, so not updating periodically\");\n    60→      return;\n    61→    }\n    62→\n    63→    computeMarketSummary();\n    64→    mkSummaryUpdateEvent.fireAsync(\"MarketSummaryUpdate\");\n    65→  }\n    66→\n    67→  @Lock(LockType.READ)\n    68→  public MarketSummaryDataBean getMarketSummaryDataBean() {\n    69→    if (marketSummaryDataBean == null) {\n    70→      computeMarketSummary();\n    71→    }\n    72→    return marketSummaryDataBean;\n    73→  }\n    74→\n    75→  private void computeMarketSummary() {\n    76→    List<QuoteDataBean> quotes;\n    77→\n    78→    try {\n    79→      CriteriaBuilder criteriaBuilder = entityManager.getCriteriaBuilder();\n    80→      CriteriaQuery<QuoteDataBean> criteriaQuery = criteriaBuilder.createQuery(QuoteDataBean.class);\n    81→      Root<QuoteDataBean> quoteRoot = criteriaQuery.from(QuoteDataBean.class);\n    82→      criteriaQuery.orderBy(criteriaBuilder.desc(quoteRoot.get(\"change1\")));\n    83→      criteriaQuery.select(quoteRoot);\n    84→      TypedQuery<QuoteDataBean> q = entityManager.createQuery(criteriaQuery);\n    85→      quotes = q.getResultList();\n    86→    } catch (Exception e) {\n    87→      Log.debug(\"Warning: The database has not been configured.\");\n    88→      return;\n    89→    }\n    90→\n    91→    QuoteDataBean[] quoteArray = quotes.toArray(new QuoteDataBean[quotes.size()]);\n    92→    ArrayList<QuoteDataBean> topGainers = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>(5);\n    93→    ArrayList<QuoteDataBean> topLosers = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>(5);\n    94→    BigDecimal TSIA = FinancialUtils.ZERO;\n    95→    BigDecimal openTSIA = FinancialUtils.ZERO;\n    96→    double totalVolume = 0.0;\n    97→\n    98→    if (quoteArray.length > 5) {\n    99→      for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {\n   100→        topGainers.add(quoteArray[i]);\n   101→      }\n   102→      for (int i = quoteArray.length - 1; i >= quoteArray.length - 5; i--) {\n   103→        topLosers.add(quoteArray[i]);\n   104→      }\n   105→\n   106→      for (QuoteDataBean quote : quoteArray) {\n   107→        BigDecimal price = quote.getPrice();\n   108→        BigDecimal open = quote.getOpen();\n   109→        double volume = quote.getVolume();\n   110→        TSIA = TSIA.add(price);\n   111→        openTSIA = openTSIA.add(open);\n   112→        totalVolume += volume;\n   113→      }\n   114→      TSIA = TSIA.divide(new BigDecimal(quoteArray.length), FinancialUtils.ROUND);\n   115→      openTSIA = openTSIA.divide(new BigDecimal(quoteArray.length), FinancialUtils.ROUND);\n   116→    }\n   117→\n   118→    setMarketSummaryDataBean(new MarketSummaryDataBean(TSIA, openTSIA, totalVolume, topGainers, topLosers));\n   119→  }\n   120→\n   121→  @Lock(LockType.WRITE)\n   122→  public void setMarketSummaryDataBean(MarketSummaryDataBean marketSummaryDataBean) {\n   123→    this.marketSummaryDataBean = marketSummaryDataBean;\n   124→  }\n   125→}\n   126→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0505b85d-7bd5-4c52-85f6-40bd7ce1ee5d","uuid":"1c93ca26-efbe-4a27-a08e-13a4f3004e93"}
