{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011kb9BgZE4pDobPsexLzWVf","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging;\n    17→\n    18→/**\n    19→ * MIGRATION NOTES:\n    20→ * \n    21→ * Original: JMS TextMessage with properties (command, orderID, twoPhase, direct, publishTime)\n    22→ * Quarkus: Plain Java object (POJO) used with Reactive Messaging\n    23→ * \n    24→ * In Jakarta EE, JMS messages were heavyweight with:\n    25→ * - message.setStringProperty(\"command\", \"neworder\")\n    26→ * - message.setIntProperty(\"orderID\", orderID)\n    27→ * - message.setBooleanProperty(\"twoPhase\", twoPhase)\n    28→ * - message.setText(...)\n    29→ * \n    30→ * In Quarkus, we use simple POJOs that are serialized automatically.\n    31→ * This is cleaner, type-safe, and doesn't require JMS infrastructure.\n    32→ */\n    33→public class OrderMessage {\n    34→    \n    35→    public static final String COMMAND_NEW_ORDER = \"neworder\";\n    36→    public static final String COMMAND_PING = \"ping\";\n    37→    \n    38→    private String command;\n    39→    private Integer orderID;\n    40→    private boolean twoPhase;\n    41→    private boolean direct;\n    42→    private long publishTime;\n    43→    private String text;\n    44→    \n    45→    // Default constructor for serialization\n    46→    public OrderMessage() {\n    47→    }\n    48→    \n    49→    // Factory method for new order messages\n    50→    public static OrderMessage newOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) {\n    51→        OrderMessage msg = new OrderMessage();\n    52→        msg.command = COMMAND_NEW_ORDER;\n    53→        msg.orderID = orderID;\n    54→        msg.twoPhase = twoPhase;\n    55→        msg.direct = false;\n    56→        msg.publishTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n    57→        msg.text = \"Order message for orderID=\" + orderID;\n    58→        return msg;\n    59→    }\n    60→    \n    61→    // Factory method for ping messages\n    62→    public static OrderMessage ping(String text) {\n    63→        OrderMessage msg = new OrderMessage();\n    64→        msg.command = COMMAND_PING;\n    65→        msg.publishTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n    66→        msg.text = text;\n    67→        return msg;\n    68→    }\n    69→    \n    70→    // Getters and setters\n    71→    public String getCommand() {\n    72→        return command;\n    73→    }\n    74→    \n    75→    public void setCommand(String command) {\n    76→        this.command = command;\n    77→    }\n    78→    \n    79→    public Integer getOrderID() {\n    80→        return orderID;\n    81→    }\n    82→    \n    83→    public void setOrderID(Integer orderID) {\n    84→        this.orderID = orderID;\n    85→    }\n    86→    \n    87→    public boolean isTwoPhase() {\n    88→        return twoPhase;\n    89→    }\n    90→    \n    91→    public void setTwoPhase(boolean twoPhase) {\n    92→        this.twoPhase = twoPhase;\n    93→    }\n    94→    \n    95→    public boolean isDirect() {\n    96→        return direct;\n    97→    }\n    98→    \n    99→    public void setDirect(boolean direct) {\n   100→        this.direct = direct;\n   101→    }\n   102→    \n   103→    public long getPublishTime() {\n   104→        return publishTime;\n   105→    }\n   106→    \n   107→    public void setPublishTime(long publishTime) {\n   108→        this.publishTime = publishTime;\n   109→    }\n   110→    \n   111→    public String getText() {\n   112→        return text;\n   113→    }\n   114→    \n   115→    public void setText(String text) {\n   116→        this.text = text;\n   117→    }\n   118→    \n   119→    @Override\n   120→    public String toString() {\n   121→        return \"OrderMessage{\" +\n   122→                \"command='\" + command + '\\'' +\n   123→                \", orderID=\" + orderID +\n   124→                \", twoPhase=\" + twoPhase +\n   125→                \", publishTime=\" + publishTime +\n   126→                '}';\n   127→    }\n   128→}\n   129→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0505b85d-7bd5-4c52-85f6-40bd7ce1ee5d","uuid":"108fe9b1-6ccd-4c22-ad39-e4ca195b957f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014WnCe6y6cehrcX3t3rWtmG","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→\n    20→/**\n    21→ * MIGRATION NOTES:\n    22→ * \n    23→ * Original: JMS TextMessage published to jms/TradeStreamerTopic\n    24→ * Properties: command, symbol, price, oldPrice, publishTime\n    25→ * \n    26→ * Quarkus: Simple POJO with same information, used with Reactive Messaging.\n    27→ * \n    28→ * The DTStreamer3MDB consumed topic messages for:\n    29→ * - \"updateQuote\" command: Log price changes\n    30→ * - \"ping\" command: Health check / performance testing\n    31→ */\n    32→public class QuoteUpdateMessage {\n    33→    \n    34→    public static final String COMMAND_UPDATE_QUOTE = \"updateQuote\";\n    35→    public static final String COMMAND_PING = \"ping\";\n    36→    \n    37→    private String command;\n    38→    private String symbol;\n    39→    private BigDecimal price;\n    40→    private BigDecimal oldPrice;\n    41→    private long publishTime;\n    42→    private String text;\n    43→    \n    44→    // Additional fields for full quote update (matching original JMS message properties)\n    45→    private String company;\n    46→    private BigDecimal open;\n    47→    private BigDecimal low;\n    48→    private BigDecimal high;\n    49→    private double volume;\n    50→    private BigDecimal changeFactor;\n    51→    private double sharesTraded;\n    52→    \n    53→    // Default constructor for serialization\n    54→    public QuoteUpdateMessage() {\n    55→    }\n    56→    \n    57→    // Factory method for quote update\n    58→    public static QuoteUpdateMessage quoteUpdate(String symbol, BigDecimal newPrice, BigDecimal oldPrice) {\n    59→        QuoteUpdateMessage msg = new QuoteUpdateMessage();\n    60→        msg.command = COMMAND_UPDATE_QUOTE;\n    61→        msg.symbol = symbol;\n    62→        msg.price = newPrice;\n    63→        msg.oldPrice = oldPrice;\n    64→        msg.publishTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n    65→        msg.text = \"Quote update for \" + symbol + \": \" + oldPrice + \" -> \" + newPrice;\n    66→        return msg;\n    67→    }\n    68→    \n    69→    // Factory method for ping\n    70→    public static QuoteUpdateMessage ping(String text) {\n    71→        QuoteUpdateMessage msg = new QuoteUpdateMessage();\n    72→        msg.command = COMMAND_PING;\n    73→        msg.publishTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n    74→        msg.text = text;\n    75→        return msg;\n    76→    }\n    77→    \n    78→    // Getters and setters\n    79→    public String getCommand() {\n    80→        return command;\n    81→    }\n    82→    \n    83→    public void setCommand(String command) {\n    84→        this.command = command;\n    85→    }\n    86→    \n    87→    public String getSymbol() {\n    88→        return symbol;\n    89→    }\n    90→    \n    91→    public void setSymbol(String symbol) {\n    92→        this.symbol = symbol;\n    93→    }\n    94→    \n    95→    public BigDecimal getPrice() {\n    96→        return price;\n    97→    }\n    98→    \n    99→    public void setPrice(BigDecimal price) {\n   100→        this.price = price;\n   101→    }\n   102→    \n   103→    public BigDecimal getOldPrice() {\n   104→        return oldPrice;\n   105→    }\n   106→    \n   107→    public void setOldPrice(BigDecimal oldPrice) {\n   108→        this.oldPrice = oldPrice;\n   109→    }\n   110→    \n   111→    public long getPublishTime() {\n   112→        return publishTime;\n   113→    }\n   114→    \n   115→    public void setPublishTime(long publishTime) {\n   116→        this.publishTime = publishTime;\n   117→    }\n   118→    \n   119→    public String getText() {\n   120→        return text;\n   121→    }\n   122→    \n   123→    public void setText(String text) {\n   124→        this.text = text;\n   125→    }\n   126→    \n   127→    // Additional getters/setters for full quote update fields\n   128→    public String getCompany() {\n   129→        return company;\n   130→    }\n   131→    \n   132→    public void setCompany(String company) {\n   133→        this.company = company;\n   134→    }\n   135→    \n   136→    public BigDecimal getOpen() {\n   137→        return open;\n   138→    }\n   139→    \n   140→    public void setOpen(BigDecimal open) {\n   141→        this.open = open;\n   142→    }\n   143→    \n   144→    public BigDecimal getLow() {\n   145→        return low;\n   146→    }\n   147→    \n   148→    public void setLow(BigDecimal low) {\n   149→        this.low = low;\n   150→    }\n   151→    \n   152→    public BigDecimal getHigh() {\n   153→        return high;\n   154→    }\n   155→    \n   156→    public void setHigh(BigDecimal high) {\n   157→        this.high = high;\n   158→    }\n   159→    \n   160→    public double getVolume() {\n   161→        return volume;\n   162→    }\n   163→    \n   164→    public void setVolume(double volume) {\n   165→        this.volume = volume;\n   166→    }\n   167→    \n   168→    public BigDecimal getChangeFactor() {\n   169→        return changeFactor;\n   170→    }\n   171→    \n   172→    public void setChangeFactor(BigDecimal changeFactor) {\n   173→        this.changeFactor = changeFactor;\n   174→    }\n   175→    \n   176→    public double getSharesTraded() {\n   177→        return sharesTraded;\n   178→    }\n   179→    \n   180→    public void setSharesTraded(double sharesTraded) {\n   181→        this.sharesTraded = sharesTraded;\n   182→    }\n   183→    \n   184→    @Override\n   185→    public String toString() {\n   186→        return \"QuoteUpdateMessage{\" +\n   187→                \"command='\" + command + '\\'' +\n   188→                \", symbol='\" + symbol + '\\'' +\n   189→                \", price=\" + price +\n   190→                \", oldPrice=\" + oldPrice +\n   191→                \", publishTime=\" + publishTime +\n   192→                '}';\n   193→    }\n   194→}\n   195→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0505b85d-7bd5-4c52-85f6-40bd7ce1ee5d","uuid":"90788fbe-f1c2-4157-af69-b07c656cdc89"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016EoXVRQQBSnRrKsshp6DMH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→FROM maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble\n     2→\n     3→USER root\n     4→# install uv\n     5→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl lsof python3-venv python3-full     && curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\n     6→\n     7→ENV PATH=\"/root/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n     8→\n     9→# Shared browsers path so Chromium is cached once\n    10→ENV PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH=/ms-playwright\n    11→RUN mkdir -p /ms-playwright && chmod 755 /ms-playwright\n    12→\n    13→# create venv and install\n    14→RUN uv venv /opt/venv     && uv pip install --python /opt/venv/bin/python playwright==1.47.0 pytest\n    15→\n    16→ENV PATH=\"/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\n    17→RUN playwright install --with-deps chromium\n    18→\n    19→# Set working directory\n    20→WORKDIR /app\n    21→\n    22→# Copy all the assets\n    23→COPY . .\n    24→\n    25→RUN if [ -f mvnw ]; then chmod +x mvnw; fi && if [ -f smoke.py ]; then chmod +x smoke.py; fi\n    26→\n    27→# Build the application at image build time\n    28→RUN mvn clean install -DskipTests\n    29→\n    30→CMD [\"mvn\", \"quarkus:run\"]\n    31→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0505b85d-7bd5-4c52-85f6-40bd7ce1ee5d","uuid":"2b11e3e8-9391-4f5d-b386-16e3eccce13a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RRL36dTe63uw5uhujVXD7b","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.mdb;\n    17→\n    18→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n    19→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    20→import jakarta.enterprise.event.ObservesAsync;\n    21→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    22→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    23→\n    24→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    25→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging.OrderMessage;\n    26→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    27→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.MDBStats;\n    28→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TimerStat;\n    29→\n    30→/**\n    31→ * MIGRATION: Quarkus @Incoming(\"trade-broker-queue\") -> Jakarta EE CDI @ObservesAsync\n    32→ */\n    33→@ApplicationScoped\n    34→public class DTBroker3MDB {\n    35→\n    36→  private final MDBStats mdbStats;\n    37→  private int statInterval = 10000;\n    38→\n    39→  @Inject\n    40→  TradeServices trade;\n    41→\n    42→  public DTBroker3MDB() {\n    43→    if (statInterval <= 0) {\n    44→      statInterval = 10000;\n    45→    }\n    46→    mdbStats = MDBStats.getInstance();\n    47→  }\n    48→\n    49→  @PostConstruct\n    50→  void init() {\n    51→    Log.trace(\"DTBroker3MDB:init()\");\n    52→  }\n    53→\n    54→  @Transactional\n    55→  public void onMessage(@ObservesAsync OrderMessage message) {\n    56→    try {\n    57→      Log.trace(\"TradeBroker:onMessage -- received message -->\" + message.getText() + \"command-->\"\n    58→          + message.getCommand() + \"<--\");\n    59→\n    60→      String command = message.getCommand();\n    61→      if (command == null) {\n    62→        Log.debug(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage -- received message with null command. Message-->\" + message);\n    63→        return;\n    64→      }\n    65→      if (command.equalsIgnoreCase(\"neworder\")) {\n    66→        Integer orderID = message.getOrderID();\n    67→        boolean twoPhase = message.isTwoPhase();\n    68→        long publishTime = message.getPublishTime();\n    69→        long receiveTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n    70→\n    71→        try {\n    72→          Log.trace(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage - completing order \" + orderID + \" twoPhase=\" + twoPhase);\n    73→          trade.completeOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n    74→\n    75→          TimerStat currentStats = mdbStats.addTiming(\"DTBroker3MDB:neworder\", publishTime, receiveTime);\n    76→\n    77→          if ((currentStats.getCount() % statInterval) == 0) {\n    78→            Log.log(\" DTBroker3MDB: processed \" + statInterval + \" stock trading orders.\" +\n    79→                \" Total NewOrders process = \" + currentStats.getCount() +\n    80→                \"Time (in seconds):\" +\n    81→                \" min: \" + currentStats.getMinSecs() +\n    82→                \" max: \" + currentStats.getMaxSecs() +\n    83→                \" avg: \" + currentStats.getAvgSecs());\n    84→          }\n    85→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    86→          Log.error(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage Exception completing order: \" + orderID + \"\\n\", e);\n    87→          throw new RuntimeException(\"Failed to complete order: \" + orderID, e);\n    88→        }\n    89→      } else if (command.equalsIgnoreCase(\"ping\")) {\n    90→        Log.trace(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage  received test command -- message: \" + message.getText());\n    91→\n    92→        long publishTime = message.getPublishTime();\n    93→        long receiveTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n    94→\n    95→        TimerStat currentStats = mdbStats.addTiming(\"DTBroker3MDB:ping\", publishTime, receiveTime);\n    96→\n    97→        if ((currentStats.getCount() % statInterval) == 0) {\n    98→          Log.log(\" DTBroker3MDB: received \" + statInterval + \" ping messages.\" +\n    99→              \" Total ping message count = \" + currentStats.getCount() +\n   100→              \" Time (in seconds):\" +\n   101→              \" min: \" + currentStats.getMinSecs() +\n   102→              \" max: \" + currentStats.getMaxSecs() +\n   103→              \" avg: \" + currentStats.getAvgSecs());\n   104→        }\n   105→      } else {\n   106→        Log.error(\"DTBroker3MDB:onMessage - unknown message request command-->\" + command + \"<-- message=\" + message.getText());\n   107→      }\n   108→    } catch (Throwable t) {\n   109→      Log.error(\"DTBroker3MDB: Exception\", t);\n   110→      throw new RuntimeException(\"DTBroker3MDB processing failed\", t);\n   111→    }\n   112→  }\n   113→}\n   114→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0505b85d-7bd5-4c52-85f6-40bd7ce1ee5d","uuid":"eb8da466-c424-4e2c-a1e6-9ffb21469c4e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GkpZso2DbTLTVqQCqGo2a5","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\n    17→\n    18→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans.RunStatsDataBean;\n    19→\n    20→public interface TradeDB {\n    21→  \n    22→  /**\n    23→   * Reset the TradeData by - removing all newly registered users by scenario\n    24→   * servlet (i.e. users with userID's beginning with \"ru:\") * - removing all\n    25→   * buy/sell order pairs - setting logoutCount = loginCount\n    26→   *\n    27→   * return statistics for this benchmark run\n    28→   */\n    29→  RunStatsDataBean resetTrade(boolean deleteAll) throws Exception;\n    30→\n    31→  /**\n    32→   * Get the Database Product Name\n    33→   *\n    34→   * return DB Product Name String\n    35→   */\n    36→  String checkDBProductName() throws Exception;\n    37→\n    38→  /**\n    39→   * Get the impl for the TradeService\n    40→   *\n    41→   * return int matching the implementation\n    42→   */\n    43→\n    44→}\n    45→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0505b85d-7bd5-4c52-85f6-40bd7ce1ee5d","uuid":"55c88cca-bb7a-4bb0-ba65-4a133d093d18"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01MWP5SypLBF22z5411zYKWA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good, I now have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Let me now create all the missing files in parallel using Task agents. I need to:\n1. Create DirectSLSBBean.java (session2direct delegate)\n2. Create TradeResource.java (JAX-RS trade endpoints)\n3. Create QuoteResource.java (JAX-RS quote endpoints) \n4. Create MessagingResource.java (JAX-RS messaging endpoints)\n5. Create TradeAppResource.java (web UI)\n6. Update TradeDirectDBUtils.java (fix DataSource injection)\n7. Update Dockerfile for Open Liberty\n\nLet me launch these in parallel:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7560,"cache_read_input_tokens":84433,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7560,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":7641},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0505b85d-7bd5-4c52-85f6-40bd7ce1ee5d","uuid":"c8e3359f-4f97-4b5e-a3d9-adb8cec25523"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01MWP5SypLBF22z5411zYKWA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01JEbw6dAcur8mwwwWpaCaaX","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Create DirectSLSBBean.java","prompt":"Create the file `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/session2direct/DirectSLSBBean.java` with the following content. This is a Jakarta EE migration of the Quarkus DayTrader application. This class delegates to the TradeDirect JDBC implementation.\n\nThe file should be:\n\n```java\n/**\n * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n *\n * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n *\n * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n *\n * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n * limitations under the License.\n */\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.session2direct;\n\nimport java.math.BigDecimal;\nimport java.util.Collection;\nimport java.util.concurrent.Future;\n\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.inject.Any;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.inject.Instance;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\n\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans.MarketSummaryDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.OrderDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.RuntimeMode;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeJDBC;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeSession2Direct;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\n@TradeSession2Direct\n@RuntimeMode(\"Session to Direct\")\n@Trace\npublic class DirectSLSBBean implements TradeServices {\n\n    @Inject\n    @TradeJDBC\n    Instance<TradeServices> tradeDirect;\n\n    private TradeServices getTradeDirect() {\n        TradeServices ts = tradeDirect.get();\n        ts.setInSession(true);\n        return ts;\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public MarketSummaryDataBean getMarketSummary() throws Exception {\n        return getTradeDirect().getMarketSummary();\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public OrderDataBean buy(String userID, String symbol, double quantity, int orderProcessingMode) throws Exception {\n        return getTradeDirect().buy(userID, symbol, quantity, orderProcessingMode);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public OrderDataBean sell(String userID, Integer holdingID, int orderProcessingMode) throws Exception {\n        return getTradeDirect().sell(userID, holdingID, orderProcessingMode);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public void queueOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception {\n        getTradeDirect().queueOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public OrderDataBean completeOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception {\n        return getTradeDirect().completeOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public Future<OrderDataBean> completeOrderAsync(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception {\n        return getTradeDirect().completeOrderAsync(orderID, twoPhase);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public void cancelOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception {\n        getTradeDirect().cancelOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public void orderCompleted(String userID, Integer orderID) throws Exception {\n        getTradeDirect().orderCompleted(userID, orderID);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public Collection<?> getOrders(String userID) throws Exception {\n        return getTradeDirect().getOrders(userID);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public Collection<?> getClosedOrders(String userID) throws Exception {\n        return getTradeDirect().getClosedOrders(userID);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public QuoteDataBean createQuote(String symbol, String companyName, BigDecimal price) throws Exception {\n        return getTradeDirect().createQuote(symbol, companyName, price);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public QuoteDataBean getQuote(String symbol) throws Exception {\n        return getTradeDirect().getQuote(symbol);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public Collection<?> getAllQuotes() throws Exception {\n        return getTradeDirect().getAllQuotes();\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public QuoteDataBean updateQuotePriceVolume(String symbol, BigDecimal newPrice, double sharesTraded) throws Exception {\n        return getTradeDirect().updateQuotePriceVolume(symbol, newPrice, sharesTraded);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public Collection<HoldingDataBean> getHoldings(String userID) throws Exception {\n        return getTradeDirect().getHoldings(userID);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public HoldingDataBean getHolding(Integer holdingID) throws Exception {\n        return getTradeDirect().getHolding(holdingID);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public AccountDataBean getAccountData(String userID) throws Exception {\n        return getTradeDirect().getAccountData(userID);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public AccountProfileDataBean getAccountProfileData(String userID) throws Exception {\n        return getTradeDirect().getAccountProfileData(userID);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public AccountProfileDataBean updateAccountProfile(AccountProfileDataBean profileData) throws Exception {\n        return getTradeDirect().updateAccountProfile(profileData);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public AccountDataBean login(String userID, String password) throws Exception {\n        return getTradeDirect().login(userID, password);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public void logout(String userID) throws Exception {\n        getTradeDirect().logout(userID);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public AccountDataBean register(String userID, String password, String fullname, String address, String email,\n            String creditcard, BigDecimal openBalance) throws Exception {\n        return getTradeDirect().register(userID, password, fullname, address, email, creditcard, openBalance);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public OrderDataBean createOrder(AccountDataBean account, QuoteDataBean quote, HoldingDataBean holding,\n            String orderType, double quantity) throws Exception {\n        return getTradeDirect().createOrder(account, quote, holding, orderType, quantity);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public int getImpl() {\n        return TradeConfig.SESSION_TO_DIRECT;\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public QuoteDataBean pingTwoPhase(String symbol) throws Exception {\n        return getTradeDirect().pingTwoPhase(symbol);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public double investmentReturn(double rnd1, double rnd2) throws Exception {\n        return getTradeDirect().investmentReturn(rnd1, rnd2);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public void setInSession(boolean inSession) {\n        // no-op for session bean\n    }\n}\n```\n\nWrite this exact content to the file. Create any parent directories if needed.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7560,"cache_read_input_tokens":84433,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7560,"ephemeral_