{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_012rJrM4FBn4EBSnCotCnxrA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I can see the exact problem. EclipseLink is generating `ACCOUNTID INTEGER IDENTITY NOT NULL` but H2 2.2.224 expects `GENERATED BY DEFAULT AS IDENTITY`. The `H2Platform` setting in EclipseLink 4.0.9 doesn't handle this correctly for H2 2.x.\n\nThere are a few options:\n1. Downgrade H2 to 1.4.200 which accepts `INTEGER IDENTITY` syntax\n2. Provide manual DDL scripts\n3. Switch from `GenerationType.IDENTITY` to `GenerationType.AUTO` (which uses `SEQUENCE` on H2)\n\nThe simplest and most reliable approach is to provide an explicit DDL script. But actually, let me try option 3 first - changing `IDENTITY` to `AUTO` in the entity classes, since that would require EclipseLink to use its default strategy which should work better with H2.\n\nActually, let me try a cleaner approach - use `GenerationType.SEQUENCE` with explicit sequences, or better yet, just use `GenerationType.AUTO` and let EclipseLink decide:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":921,"cache_read_input_tokens":56871,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":921,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":386},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0505b85d-7bd5-4c52-85f6-40bd7ce1ee5d","uuid":"599c6a61-84d5-47aa-bdc1-c37d22f7c934"}
