{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FRZMwx15MH28tz6nRVMNao","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.Serializable;\n    19→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    20→import java.util.Date;\n    21→\n    22→// MIGRATION: javax.* -> jakarta.*\n    23→import jakarta.persistence.Column;\n    24→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n    25→import jakarta.persistence.FetchType;\n    26→import jakarta.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n    27→import jakarta.persistence.GenerationType;\n    28→import jakarta.persistence.Id;\n    29→import jakarta.persistence.JoinColumn;\n    30→import jakarta.persistence.ManyToOne;\n    31→import jakarta.persistence.NamedQueries;\n    32→import jakarta.persistence.NamedQuery;\n    33→import jakarta.persistence.OneToOne;\n    34→import jakarta.persistence.Table;\n    35→import jakarta.persistence.Temporal;\n    36→import jakarta.persistence.TemporalType;\n    37→import jakarta.persistence.Transient;\n    38→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n    39→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    40→import jakarta.validation.constraints.PastOrPresent;\n    41→import jakarta.validation.constraints.Positive;\n    42→\n    43→import jakarta.json.bind.annotation.JsonbTransient;\n    44→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    45→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    46→\n    47→@Entity(name = \"orderejb\")\n    48→@Table(name = \"orderejb\")\n    49→@NamedQueries({\n    50→    @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.findByOrderfee\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.orderFee = :orderfee\"),\n    51→    @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.findByOrderstatus\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.orderStatus = :orderstatus\"),\n    52→    @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.findByOrderid\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.orderID = :orderid\"),\n    53→    @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.findByAccountAccountid\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.account.accountID = :accountAccountid\"),\n    54→    @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.closedOrders\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.orderStatus = 'closed' AND o.account.profile.userID  = :userID\"),\n    55→    @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.completeClosedOrders\", query = \"UPDATE orderejb o SET o.orderStatus = 'completed' WHERE o.orderStatus = 'closed' AND o.account.profile.userID  = :userID\")\n    56→})\n    57→public class OrderDataBean implements Serializable {\n    58→\n    59→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 120650490200739057L;\n    60→\n    61→    // MIGRATION: Simplified ID generation for Quarkus\n    62→    @Id\n    63→    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.IDENTITY)\n    64→    @Column(name = \"ORDERID\", nullable = false)\n    65→    private Integer orderID;\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":nul