{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Fa8Rw1T41Ci17isUYtCdqk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The error persists even with the correct runtime mode. The problem is `profile.getAccount()` returning null. This is a JPA relationship issue - the `AccountProfileDataBean.account` field is `@OneToOne(mappedBy = \"profile\", fetch = FetchType.LAZY)`, and when EclipseLink loads the profile from the database, it should be able to navigate back to the account. \n\nThe issue is that `mappedBy` on a `@OneToOne` with `LAZY` fetch can sometimes not be properly populated. Let me investigate by checking if the account data is actually there:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":456,"cache_read_input_tokens":96927,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":456,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":237},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0505b85d-7bd5-4c52-85f6-40bd7ce1ee5d","uuid":"d77a6e17-df5f-46c2-8b3c-7d2c0c592832"}
